SIMPLE: smirch
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smirch
<hw>Smirch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[From the root of
<ets>smear</ets>.]</ety> <def>To smear with something which stains, or
makes dirty; to smutch; to begrime; to soil; to sully.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll . . . with a kind of umber <qex>smirch</qex> my face.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smirch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Smirch
<hw>Smirch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A smutch; a dirty
stain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smirk</ent>⟦br⟧
